WRITING.TEXT: I used a strong magnet to get the actual shades out (they #8217;re magnetic so there #8217;s no glue, super easy to do) and then I used a knife to get the shade separator plastic piece out. To give a visual, I put a knife in between the spot that I circled, [this space ](https://imgur.com/a/scTcGDR) and just popped it out (it doesn #8217;t matter if you break that part). Then I put a magnetic sheet on it and it #8217;s done! It #8217;s not going to be perfectly flat because there are things that stick out that I couldn #8217;t get off and wasn #8217;t going to attempt to, but you pretty much just can #8217;t put any shadows in the bottom of the palette or it won #8217;t close, it #8217;s not a big deal! It #8217;s a perfect travel palette cause it has a mirror. I #8217;m very happy with it
